visuals.description:
Just playing with noise.

Mouse click to generate a new seamless pattern
Press any key to save it

* I've played with noiseDetail this time to make the curves smoother

* I've used a different strategy to make the color transitions smooth

* I've used the equation of the torus to make the pattern seamless

visuals.title: square network
visuals.description: This piece started out as a doodle on a post-it note, but I had just as much fun exploring the system with code. Each step of the generation involves finding a corner where a square can be placed without intersecting another. Following these basic rules creates some really interesting patterns, and the number of variables that can be adjusted means that a huge range of images can be produced. Generation adapts to the size of the window, so the pattern may appear slightly different on different screen sizes.

visuals.title: Camouflage
visuals.description:
The algorithm works something like this:
    
-Generate a random ellipse and calculate points lying on its edge.     
-For a certain number of iterations (randomly calculated):     
  >Change each point's x and y values according to some perlin noise and some constants.     
-Repeat the last few steps.
visuals.instructions: Press  space to re-randomize. Click to change modes and re-randomize. It may take a few seconds to load.
